[Date "2021.04.14"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Decoy Tactics"]
[ChapterName "Decoy - example 1"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/J3OJwYYa/R63DYPBy"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/LampardFan08"]
[FEN "r6k/p1q3p1/2pb1p1p/3p3N/3P2QP/1P4P1/P4PK1/2R5 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2021.04.14"]
[UTCTime "07:13:18"]

{ A Decoy is the tactic to use when you want to get a piece onto a specific square, only it happens to be currently guarded by an enemy piece. What you do is launch your assault in TWO stages:
1. Send your piece to a square (as a decoy) in the hope of coaxing the enemy guard.
2. If the enemy takes the bait and leaves its guard spot, then you can implement stage 2, by sending your waiting piece to its target. }
1. Rxc6 Qf7 (1... f5) 2. Rxd6 f5 3. Qf3 a5 4. Qxd5 Qxd5+ 5. Rxd5 g6 6. Nf4 Ra6 7. Kf3 Kg8 8. Rc5 g5 9. Nd3 Kf7 10. Rxf5+ Kg6 11. Ke4 Kg7 12. hxg5 Kh7 13. Rf6 Ra8 14. Rxh6+ Kg8 15. Nc5 a4 16. Nxa4 Kf7 17. Kd3 Re8 18. f4 Re1 19. Nc3 Rg1 20. Ne4 Rd1+ 21. Ke3 Re1+ 22. Kf3 Rd1 23. Rd6 Rf1+ 24. Kg4 Ke7 25. g6 Rc1 26. g7 Rc8 27. Ra6 Kd7 28. Nf6+ Kc7 29. g8=Q Rxg8+ 30. Nxg8 Kb7 31. Re6 Kc7 32. d5 Kb7 33. Rc6 Kb8 34. d6 Ka7 35. d7 Kb7 36. Rc4 Ka6 37. d8=Q Kb7 38. Qc7+ Ka6 39. Ra4+ Kb5 40. Qc4+ Kb6 41. Ra6+ Kb7 42. Qc6+ Kb8 43. Ra8# *


